==French==

This idiom comes from the French film ''Brice de Nice''. Popular among kids, not very rude.
The complete form is "Je t'ai cassé" but you'll hear only: "Cassé!" or "J'té cassé!"

e.g: "You're like the "ç" of Surf, you don't exist" (T'es comme le ç de Surf, t'existe pas)
<BR>"You're like the "H" of Hawaii, you're useless" (T'es comme le H de Hawaii tu sers à rien)

After those exemples, just add "J'té cassé" and the gesture. (see link)
